audio.transcript: The weather in San Francisco, California, can vary, but it's commonly known for its microclimates. Generally, the city experiences cool summers, with frequent fog, especially in the early mornings and evenings. Temperatures can range from the mid-50s to the high 60s Fahrenheit (about 13 to 20 degrees Celsius). Winters are mild, with temperatures in the mid-40s to mid-50s Fahrenheit (about 7 to 13 degrees Celsius) and a chance of rain. Because of this variation, it's a good idea to dress in layers when visiting.
